# Pixxel mask service

A small FastAPI service that runs `rembg` (BiRefNet by default) for
background removal. Called by the Next.js `/api/ai/segment` route.

## Setup

```bash
python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate          # Windows: .venv\Scripts\activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
python main.py
```

## Environment

Copy this file to `.env` (or export the variables in your shell):

```env
SEGMENT_MODEL=birefnet-general-lite
SAM2_MODEL_ID=facebook/sam2-hiera-small
SAM2_CACHE_MAX=20
SAM2_MAX_CLICKS=50
DEPTH_MODEL_ID=depth-anything/Depth-Anything-V2-Small-hf
DEPTH_CACHE_MAX=20
# Cap on per-entry depth-map pixels; larger maps are recomputed
# instead of cached (bounds peak memory at ~80 MB at 20 entries).
DEPTH_CACHE_MAX_PIXELS=4194304
# Reject inputs whose longest side exceeds this; the depth model runs
# internally at ~518×518, and resizing the output back to a much
# larger resolution is O(n²) Lanczos work.
DEPTH_MAX_SIDE=2048
PORT=8001
MAX_UPLOAD_MB=24
CORS_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000,http://127.0.0.1:3000
# For NVIDIA GPU: pip install rembg[gpu]
# SEGMENT_PROVIDERS=CUDAExecutionProvider,CPUExecutionProvider
```

## Endpoints

- `GET  /health`            – service info
- `POST /segment`           – multipart `image`; returns PNG with alpha
- `POST /sam2/click`        – multipart `image` + form `clicks`; returns
                              greyscale PNG mask. 501 if torch/transformers
                              are not installed.

## Hardware

| Host                  | Auto-detected provider            |
| --------------------- | --------------------------------- |
| Linux + NVIDIA GPU    | `CUDAExecutionProvider`           |
| macOS Apple Silicon   | `CoreMLExecutionProvider`         |
| Anything else         | `CPUExecutionProvider`            |
